{"node_id": "48bf4e50f10d52778377bb03c3e22104", "title": "Add & subtract rational expressions: like denominators", "description": "Example: Add and simplify 6/(2x┬▓-7) + (-3x-8)/(2x┬▓-7).", "topic_path": ["Khan Academy (English - US curriculum)", "Math by grade", "Eureka Math/EngageNY", "Precalculus (Eureka Math/EngageNY)", "Module 3: Rational and exponential functions", "Topic B: Lessons 10-11: Adding & subtracting rational expressions", "Add & subtract rational expressions: like denominators"], "assessment_items": [{"item_id": "2da43b577ed55b638ee599eb1bb795df", "question_content": "**Add the following rational expressions.**\n\n$\\dfrac{6}{2x^2-7}+\\dfrac{-3x-8}{2x^2-7}=$ [[Ōśā expression 1]]", "hints": ["We want to add two rational expressions *whose denominators are equal.* We can do this by adding the numerators and keeping the denominator the same.\n\n[[Ōśā explanation 1]]", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\dfrac{6}{2x^2-7}+\\dfrac{-3x-8}{2x^2-7}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{(6)+(-3x-8)}{2x^2-7}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{6-3x-8}{2x^2-7}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{-3x-2}{2x^2-7}\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\dfrac{6}{2x^2-7}+\\dfrac{-3x-8}{2x^2-7}=\\dfrac{-3x-2}{2x^2-7}$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["\\frac{-3x-2}{2x^2-7}", "\\frac{3x+2}{7-2x^2}"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": true, "key": 0, "value": "\\frac{-3x-2}{2x^2-7}"}, {"considered": "correct", "form": true, "key": 1, "simplify": false, "value": "\\frac{3x+2}{7-2x^2}"}]}}}, {"item_id": "c3ddd0dea1a65b70b513970fc96087dc", "question_content": "**Add the following rational expressions.**\n\n$\\dfrac{14}{y^2+47}+\\dfrac{2y^2-7}{y^2+47}=$ [[Ōśā expression 1]]", "hints": ["We want to add two rational expressions *whose denominators are equal.* We can do this by adding the numerators and keeping the denominator the same.\n\n[[Ōśā explanation 1]]", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\dfrac{14}{y^2+47}+\\dfrac{2y^2-7}{y^2+47}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{(14)+(2y^2-7)}{y^2+47}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{14+2y^2-7}{y^2+47}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{2y^2+7}{y^2+47}\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\dfrac{14}{y^2+47}+\\dfrac{2y^2-7}{y^2+47}=\\dfrac{2y^2+7}{y^2+47}$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["\\frac{2y^2+7}{y^2+47}"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": true, "key": 0, "value": "\\frac{2y^2+7}{y^2+47}"}]}}}, {"item_id": "70582f2cf3c4596c94308c860a27d45e", "question_content": "**Add the following rational expressions.**\n\n$\\dfrac{z^2}{z^3+4}+\\dfrac{4z^2-6z}{z^3+4}=$ [[Ōśā expression 1]]", "hints": ["We want to add two rational expressions *whose denominators are equal.* We can do this by adding the numerators and keeping the denominator the same.\n\n[[Ōśā explanation 1]]", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\dfrac{z^2}{z^3+4}+\\dfrac{4z^2-6z}{z^3+4}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{(z^2)+(4z^2-6z)}{z^3+4}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{z^2+4z^2-6z}{z^3+4}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{5z^2-6z}{z^3+4}\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\dfrac{z^2}{z^3+4}+\\dfrac{4z^2-6z}{z^3+4}=\\dfrac{5z^2-6z}{z^3+4}$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["\\frac{5z^2-6z}{z^3+4}"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": true, "key": 0, "value": "\\frac{5z^2-6z}{z^3+4}"}]}}}, {"item_id": "293a526f40885b249c32d477754d561f", "question_content": "**Add the following rational expressions.**\n\n$\\dfrac{k^3}{k+5}+\\dfrac{7k^3+3}{k+5}=$ [[Ōśā expression 1]]", "hints": ["We want to add two rational expressions *whose denominators are equal.* We can do this by adding the numerators and keeping the denominator the same.\n\n[[Ōśā explanation 1]]", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\dfrac{k^3}{k+5}+\\dfrac{7k^3+3}{k+5}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{(k^3)+(7k^3+3)}{k+5}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{k^3+7k^3+3}{k+5}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{8k^3+3}{k+5}\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\dfrac{k^3}{k+5}+\\dfrac{7k^3+3}{k+5}=\\dfrac{8k^3+3}{k+5}$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["\\frac{8k^3+3}{k+5}"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": true, "key": 0, "value": "\\frac{8k^3+3}{k+5}"}]}}}, {"item_id": "87641ec9de795d9da0bfeda3cc8ee93e", "question_content": "**Add the following rational expressions.**\n\n$\\dfrac{-m+6}{m^2-16}+\\dfrac{2m-2}{m^2-16}=$ [[Ōśā expression 1]]", "hints": ["We want to add two rational expressions *whose denominators are equal.* We can do this by adding the numerators and keeping the denominator the same.\n\n[[Ōśā explanation 1]]", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\dfrac{-m+6}{m^2-16}+\\dfrac{2m-2}{m^2-16}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{(-m+6)+(2m-2)}{m^2-16}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{-m+6+2m-2}{m^2-16}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{m+4}{m^2-16}\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\dfrac{-m+6}{m^2-16}+\\dfrac{2m-2}{m^2-16}=\\dfrac{m+4}{m^2-16}$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["\\frac{m+4}{m^2-16}", "\\frac{1}{m-4}"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": true, "key": 0, "value": "\\frac{m+4}{m^2-16}"}, {"considered": "correct", "form": false, "key": 1, "simplify": false, "value": "\\frac{1}{m-4}"}]}}}, {"item_id": "30b02bdf5413568a9e7d179fe3516fe7", "question_content": "**Add the following rational expressions.**\n\n$\\dfrac{3x-10}{9x^2+18x+9}+\\dfrac{-6x+3}{9x^2+18x+9}=$ [[Ōśā expression 1]]", "hints": ["We want to add two rational expressions *whose denominators are equal.* We can do this by adding the numerators and keeping the denominator the same.\n\n[[Ōśā explanation 1]]", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\dfrac{3x-10}{9x^2+18x+9}+\\dfrac{-6x+3}{9x^2+18x+9}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{(3x-10)+(-6x+3)}{9x^2+18x+9}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{3x-10-6x+3}{9x^2+18x+9}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{-3x-7}{9x^2+18x+9}\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\dfrac{3x-10}{9x^2+18x+9}+\\dfrac{-6x+3}{9x^2+18x+9}=\\dfrac{-3x-7}{9x^2+18x+9}$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["\\frac{-\\left(3x+7\\right)}{9x^2+18x+9}", "\\frac{\\left(3x+7\\right)}{-\\left(9x^2+18x+9\\right)}", "\\frac{-\\left(3x+7\\right)}{9\\left(x^2+2x+1\\right)}", "\\frac{\\left(3x+7\\right)}{-9\\left(x^2+2x+1\\right)}", "\\frac{-\\left(3x+7\\right)}{9\\left(x+1\\right)\\left(x+1\\right)}", "\\frac{\\left(3x+7\\right)}{-9\\left(x+1\\right)\\left(x+1\\right)}", "\\frac{-\\left(3x+7\\right)}{9\\left(x+1\\right)^2}", "\\frac{\\left(3x+7\\right)}{-9\\left(x+1\\right)^2}"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": true, "key": 0, "value": "\\frac{-\\left(3x+7\\right)}{9x^2+18x+9}"}, {"considered": "correct", "form": true, "key": 1, "simplify": false, "value": "\\frac{\\left(3x+7\\right)}{-\\left(9x^2+18x+9\\right)}"}, {"considered": "correct", "form": true, "key": 2, "simplify": false, "value": "\\frac{-\\left(3x+7\\right)}{9\\left(x^2+2x+1\\right)}"}, {"considered": "correct", "form": true, "key": 3, "simplify": false, "value": "\\frac{\\left(3x+7\\right)}{-9\\left(x^2+2x+1\\right)}"}, {"considered": "correct", "form": true, "key": 4, "simplify": false, "value": "\\frac{-\\left(3x+7\\right)}{9\\left(x+1\\right)\\left(x+1\\right)}"}, {"considered": "correct", "form": true, "key": 5, "simplify": false, "value": "\\frac{\\left(3x+7\\right)}{-9\\left(x+1\\right)\\left(x+1\\right)}"}, {"considered": "correct", "form": false, "key": 6, "simplify": false, "value": "\\frac{-\\left(3x+7\\right)}{9\\left(x+1\\right)^2}"}, {"considered": "correct", "form": false, "key": 7, "simplify": false, "value": "\\frac{\\left(3x+7\\right)}{-9\\left(x+1\\right)^2}"}]}}}, {"item_id": "db8137fe194c5e05bc05f8de0ee116c7", "question_content": "**Add the following rational expressions.**\n\n$\\dfrac{y^3-8y^2+13}{7y^2+25}+\\dfrac{-3y+17}{7y^2+25}=$ [[Ōśā expression 1]]", "hints": ["We want to add two rational expressions *whose denominators are equal.* We can do this by adding the numerators and keeping the denominator the same.\n\n[[Ōśā explanation 1]]", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\dfrac{y^3-8y^2+13}{7y^2+25}+\\dfrac{-3y+17}{7y^2+25}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{(y^3-\\!8y^2+13)+(-3y+17)}{7y^2+25}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{y^3-8y^2+13-3y+17}{7y^2+25}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{y^3-8y^2-3y+30}{7y^2+25}\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\dfrac{y^3-8y^2+13}{7y^2+25}+\\dfrac{-3y+17}{7y^2+25}=\\dfrac{y^3-8y^2-3y+30}{7y^2+25}$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["\\frac{y^3-8y^2-3y+30}{7y^2+25}"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": true, "key": 0, "value": "\\frac{y^3-8y^2-3y+30}{7y^2+25}"}]}}}, {"item_id": "f3d48d9334e55063b58847e08637a4e1", "question_content": "**Add the following rational expressions.**\n\n$\\dfrac{2z^2-3z}{z^2+1}+\\dfrac{4z+2}{z^2+1}=$ [[Ōśā expression 1]]", "hints": ["We want to add two rational expressions *whose denominators are equal.* We can do this by adding the numerators and keeping the denominator the same.\n\n[[Ōśā explanation 1]]", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\dfrac{2z^2-3z}{z^2+1}+\\dfrac{4z+2}{z^2+1}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{(2z^2-3z)+(4z+2)}{z^2+1}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{2z^2-3z+4z+2}{z^2+1}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{2z^2+z+2}{z^2+1}\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\dfrac{2z^2-3z}{z^2+1}+\\dfrac{4z+2}{z^2+1}=\\dfrac{2z^2+z+2}{z^2+1}$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["\\frac{2z^2+z+2}{z^2+1}"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": true, "key": 0, "value": "\\frac{2z^2+z+2}{z^2+1}"}]}}}, {"item_id": "0d23dfe65e905200a39a7dc20077cd48", "question_content": "**Add the following rational expressions.**\n\n$\\dfrac{8k^2+4}{5k^2+5}+\\dfrac{k^3-k+8}{5k^2+5}=$ [[Ōśā expression 1]]", "hints": ["We want to add two rational expressions *whose denominators are equal.* We can do this by adding the numerators and keeping the denominator the same.\n\n[[Ōśā explanation 1]]", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\dfrac{8k^2+4}{5k^2+5}+\\dfrac{k^3-k+8}{5k^2+5}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{(8k^2+4)+(k^3-k+8)}{5k^2+5}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{8k^2+4+k^3-k+8}{5k^2+5}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{k^3+8k^2-k+12}{5k^2+5}\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\dfrac{8k^2+4}{5k^2+5}+\\dfrac{k^3-k+8}{5k^2+5}=\\dfrac{k^3+8k^2-k+12}{5k^2+5}$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["\\frac{k^3+8k^2-k+12}{5k^2+5}", "\\frac{k^3+8k^2-k+12}{5\\left(k^2+1\\right)}"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": true, "key": 0, "value": "\\frac{k^3+8k^2-k+12}{5k^2+5}"}, {"considered": "correct", "form": false, "key": 1, "simplify": false, "value": "\\frac{k^3+8k^2-k+12}{5\\left(k^2+1\\right)}"}]}}}, {"item_id": "6c9aac93f4555156a7860d147cfb579f", "question_content": "**Add the following rational expressions.**\n\n$\\dfrac{25}{7m^2+9}+\\dfrac{14m-11}{7m^2+9}=$ [[Ōśā expression 1]]", "hints": ["We want to add two rational expressions *whose denominators are equal.* We can do this by adding the numerators and keeping the denominator the same.\n\n[[Ōśā explanation 1]]", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\dfrac{25}{7m^2+9}+\\dfrac{14m-11}{7m^2+9}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{(25)+(14m-11)}{7m^2+9}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{25+14m-11}{7m^2+9}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{14m+14}{7m^2+9}\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\dfrac{25}{7m^2+9}+\\dfrac{14m-11}{7m^2+9}=\\dfrac{14m+14}{7m^2+9}$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["\\frac{14m+14}{7m^2+9}", "\\frac{14\\left(m+1\\right)}{7m^2+9}"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": true, "key": 0, "value": "\\frac{14m+14}{7m^2+9}"}, {"considered": "correct", "form": false, "key": 1, "simplify": false, "value": "\\frac{14\\left(m+1\\right)}{7m^2+9}"}]}}}, {"item_id": "9dd8d8c405ac50cfbedc5f720267c9f0", "question_content": "**Subtract the following rational expressions.**\n\n$\\dfrac{9x^2+3}{14x^2-9}-\\dfrac{-3x^2+5}{14x^2-9}=$ [[Ōśā expression 1]]", "hints": ["We want to subtract two rational expressions *whose denominators are equal.* We can do this by subtracting the numerators and keeping the denominator the same.\n\n[[Ōśā explanation 1]]", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\dfrac{9x^2+3}{14x^2-9}-\\dfrac{-3x^2+5}{14x^2-9}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{(9x^2+3)-(-3x^2+5)}{14x^2-9}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{9x^2+3+3x^2-5}{14x^2-9}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{12x^2-2}{14x^2-9}\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\dfrac{9x^2+3}{14x^2-9}-\\dfrac{-3x^2+5}{14x^2-9}=\\dfrac{12x^2-2}{14x^2-9}$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["\\frac{12x^2-2}{14x^2-9}", "\\frac{2\\left(6x^2-1\\right)}{14x^2-9}"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": true, "key": 0, "value": "\\frac{12x^2-2}{14x^2-9}"}, {"considered": "correct", "form": false, "key": 1, "simplify": false, "value": "\\frac{2\\left(6x^2-1\\right)}{14x^2-9}"}]}}}, {"item_id": "8287a0a6a38a57e3a1ea7b643873e990", "question_content": "**Subtract the following rational expressions.**\n\n$\\dfrac{7y^2}{y^3+4y-1}-\\dfrac{-2y^2+3y}{y^3+4y-1}=$  [[Ōśā expression 1]]", "hints": ["We want to subtract two rational expressions *whose denominators are equal.* We can do this by subtracting the numerators and keeping the denominator the same.\n\n[[Ōśā explanation 1]]", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\dfrac{7y^2}{y^3+4y-1}-\\dfrac{-2y^2+3y}{y^3+4y-1}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{(7y^2)-(-2y^2+3y)}{y^3+4y-1}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{7y^2+2y^2-3y}{y^3+4y-1}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{9y^2-3y}{y^3+4y-1}\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\dfrac{7y^2}{y^3+4y-1}-\\dfrac{-2y^2+3y}{y^3+4y-1}=\\dfrac{9y^2-3y}{y^3+4y-1}$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["\\frac{9y^2-3y}{y^3+4y-1}", "\\frac{3y\\left(3y-1\\right)}{y^3+4y-1}"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": true, "key": 0, "value": "\\frac{9y^2-3y}{y^3+4y-1}"}, {"considered": "correct", "form": false, "key": 1, "simplify": false, "value": "\\frac{3y\\left(3y-1\\right)}{y^3+4y-1}"}]}}}, {"item_id": "7ea093a9ab6a5071b5c957847fff3acd", "question_content": "**Subtract the following rational expressions.**\n\n$\\dfrac{6z+5}{13z^2+2z}-\\dfrac{7z-2}{13z^2+2z}=$ [[Ōśā expression 1]]", "hints": ["We want to subtract two rational expressions *whose denominators are equal.* We can do this by subtracting the numerators and keeping the denominator the same.\n\n[[Ōśā explanation 1]]", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\dfrac{6z+5}{13z^2+2z}-\\dfrac{7z-2}{13z^2+2z}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{(6z+5)-(7z-2)}{13z^2+2z}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{6z+5-7z+2}{13z^2+2z}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{-z+7}{13z^2+2z}\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\dfrac{6z+5}{13z^2+2z}-\\dfrac{7z-2}{13z^2+2z}=\\dfrac{-z+7}{13z^2+2z}$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["\\frac{-z+7}{13z^2+2z}", "\\frac{-z+7}{z\\left(13z+2\\right)}"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": true, "key": 0, "value": "\\frac{-z+7}{13z^2+2z}"}, {"considered": "correct", "form": true, "key": 1, "simplify": false, "value": "\\frac{-z+7}{z\\left(13z+2\\right)}"}]}}}, {"item_id": "43fa32c2863953ccbee84d9786c4b23c", "question_content": "**Subtract the following rational expressions.**\n\n$\\dfrac{4k+23}{k^2-15k}-\\dfrac{k^2+6k}{k^2-15k}=$ [[Ōśā expression 1]]", "hints": ["We want to subtract two rational expressions *whose denominators are equal.* We can do this by subtracting the numerators and keeping the denominator the same.\n\n[[Ōśā explanation 1]]", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\dfrac{4k+23}{k^2-15k}-\\dfrac{k^2+6k}{k^2-15k}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{(4k+23)-(k^2+6k)}{k^2-15k}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{4k+23-k^2-6k}{k^2-15k}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{-k^2-2k+23}{k^2-15k}\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\dfrac{4k+23}{k^2-15k}-\\dfrac{k^2+6k}{k^2-15k}=\\dfrac{-k^2-2k+23}{k^2-15k}$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["\\frac{-k^2-2k+23}{k^2-15k}", "\\frac{-k^2-2k+23}{k\\left(k-15\\right)}", "\\frac{k^2+2k-23}{-k^2+15k}", "\\frac{k^2+2k-23}{-k\\left(k-15\\right)}"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": true, "key": 0, "value": "\\frac{-k^2-2k+23}{k^2-15k}"}, {"considered": "correct", "form": true, "key": 1, "simplify": false, "value": "\\frac{-k^2-2k+23}{k\\left(k-15\\right)}"}, {"considered": "correct", "form": true, "key": 2, "simplify": false, "value": "\\frac{k^2+2k-23}{-k^2+15k}"}, {"considered": "correct", "form": true, "key": 3, "simplify": false, "value": "\\frac{k^2+2k-23}{-k\\left(k-15\\right)}"}]}}}, {"item_id": "b40badd2f1c652fbb749fd71c9fed5ac", "question_content": "**Subtract the following rational expressions.**\n\n$\\dfrac{m^3+26}{-5m^2+19}-\\dfrac{2m^3+13}{-5m^2+19}=$ [[Ōśā expression 1]]", "hints": ["We want to subtract two rational expressions *whose denominators are equal.* We can do this by subtracting the numerators and keeping the denominator the same.\n\n[[Ōśā explanation 1]]", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\dfrac{m^3+26}{-5m^2+19}-\\dfrac{2m^3+13}{-5m^2+19}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{(m^3+26)-(2m^3+13)}{-5m^2+19}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{m^3+26-2m^3-13}{-5m^2+19}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{-m^3+13}{-5m^2+19}\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\dfrac{m^3+26}{-5m^2+19}-\\dfrac{2m^3+13}{-5m^2+19}=\\dfrac{-m^3+13}{-5m^2+19}$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["\\frac{-m^3+13}{-5m^2+19}", "\\frac{m^3-13}{5m^2-19}"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": true, "key": 0, "value": "\\frac{-m^3+13}{-5m^2+19}"}, {"considered": "correct", "form": false, "key": 1, "simplify": false, "value": "\\frac{m^3-13}{5m^2-19}"}]}}}, {"item_id": "2cf6f2c369eb5576a2ee96750af7cb8f", "question_content": "**Subtract the following rational expressions.**\n\n$\\dfrac{9x^2+3}{14x^2-9}-\\dfrac{-3x^2+11}{14x^2-9}=$ [[Ōśā expression 1]]", "hints": ["We want to subtract two rational expressions *whose denominators are equal.* We can do this by subtracting the numerators and keeping the denominator the same.\n\n[[Ōśā explanation 1]]", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\dfrac{9x^2+3}{14x^2-9}-\\dfrac{-3x^2+11}{14x^2-9}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{(9x^2+3)-(-3x^2+11)}{14x^2-9}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{9x^2+3+3x^2-11}{14x^2-9}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{12x^2-8}{14x^2-9}\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\dfrac{9x^2+3}{14x^2-9}-\\dfrac{-3x^2+11}{14x^2-9}=\\dfrac{12x^2-8}{14x^2-9}$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["\\frac{12x^2-8}{14x^2-9}", "\\frac{4\\left(3x^2-2\\right)}{14x^2-9}"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": true, "key": 0, "value": "\\frac{12x^2-8}{14x^2-9}"}, {"considered": "correct", "form": true, "key": 1, "simplify": false, "value": "\\frac{4\\left(3x^2-2\\right)}{14x^2-9}"}]}}}, {"item_id": "eaa29771b8a15e3fa3d8e5eef3223ef3", "question_content": "**Subtract the following rational expressions.**\n\n$\\dfrac{11y+9}{12y^3+4y}-\\dfrac{3y^2+4}{12y^3+4y}=$ [[Ōśā expression 1]]", "hints": ["We want to subtract two rational expressions *whose denominators are equal.* We can do this by subtracting the numerators and keeping the denominator the same.\n\n[[Ōśā explanation 1]]", "$\\begin{align}\n&\\phantom{=}\\dfrac{11y+9}{12y^3+4y}-\\dfrac{3y^2+4}{12y^3+4y}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{(11y+9)-(3y^2+4)}{12y^3+4y}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{11y+9-3y^2-4}{12y^3+4y}\n\\\\\\\\\n&=\\dfrac{-3y^2+11y+5}{12y^3+4y}\n\\end{align}$", "In conclusion,\n\n$\\dfrac{11y+9}{12y^3+4y}-\\dfrac{3y^2+4}{12y^3+4y}=\\dfrac{-3y^2+11y+5}{12y^3+4y}$"], "widget_types": ["expression"], "answer_data": {"expression 1": {"type": "expression", "correct_values": ["\\frac{-3y^2+11y+5}{12y^3+4y}", "\\frac{-3y^2+11y+5}{4y\\left(3y^2+1\\right)}"], "answerForms": [{"considered": "correct", "form": true, "key": 0, "value": "\\frac{-3y^2+11y+5